about to love or exude peace.

00:02:24.630 --> 00:02:28.640 align:middle line:84%
So my wife allowed me
to come home to that.

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:31.520 align:middle line:84%
We subsequently both became
interfaith ministers,

00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:34.250 align:middle line:84%
so that's a part of
my life right now.

00:02:34.250 --> 00:02:36.120 align:middle line:90%
And I marry--

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:40.250 align:middle line:84%
I've married dozens of people
and shared my spirituality

00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:41.780 align:middle line:90%
with people.

00:02:41.780 --> 00:02:44.540 align:middle line:84%
And after I left the law,
I wanted some vehicles

00:02:44.540 --> 00:02:46.170 align:middle line:90%
for my creativity.

00:02:46.170 --> 00:02:49.220 align:middle line:84%
So I saw that there was a
spiritual drumming class,

00:02:49.220 --> 00:02:51.150 align:middle line:84%
and drumming was
always something

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:55.272 align:middle line:84%
I loved and never really gave
enough of myself over to.

00:02:55.272 --> 00:02:57.240 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMMING]

00:02:57.240 --> 00:03:00.090 align:middle line:84%
And I love the class,
and I really got into it,

00:03:00.090 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:84%
so much so that in
a matter of months,

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:07.020 align:middle line:84%
I got proficient enough to
teach and share and start

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:12.180 align:middle line:84%
drumming with Babatunde
Olatunji and some other greats.

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:16.597 align:middle line:84%
And now drumming is a huge
creative force in my life.

00:03:16.597 --> 00:03:21.467 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMMING AND CHEERING]

00:03:21.467 --> 00:03:28.300 align:middle line:90%


00:03:28.300 --> 00:03:31.730 align:middle line:84%
I surrendered to that and
gave myself over to it,

00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:33.760 align:middle line:84%
like giving yourself
over to your lover.

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:36.460 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that with
your art or yourself,

00:03:36.460 --> 00:03:38.360 align:middle line:84%
beautiful things
come out of you.

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:42.770 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMMING]

00:03:42.770 --> 00:03:48.160 align:middle line:90%


00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:49.416 align:middle line:90%
>> And bah!

00:03:49.416 --> 00:03:51.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I think my soul's
story and, really,

00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:55.570 align:middle line:84%
everybody's soul story is sort
of like the egg breaking open,

00:03:55.570 --> 00:03:58.960 align:middle line:90%
and something new can be born.

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:04.850 align:middle line:84%
The caterpillar dies, so the
butterfly can be born and fly.

00:04:04.850 --> 00:04:08.300 align:middle line:84%
Usually, we get pretty attached
to our caterpillarhood though.

00:04:08.300 --> 00:04:10.070 align:middle line:90%
It's comfortable for us.

00:04:10.070 --> 00:04:13.010 align:middle line:84%
It was comfortable being a
lawyer and making good money

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:17.060 align:middle line:84%
and having this respect of
society and my mother-in-law

00:04:17.060 --> 00:04:19.740 align:middle line:90%
and everyone else.

00:04:19.740 --> 00:04:24.510 align:middle line:84%
And yet you have to do
what's inside your heart.

00:04:24.510 --> 00:04:26.690 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to stay in
love mode as a lawyer.

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:28.415 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't up to the challenge.

00:04:28.415 --> 00:04:30.620 align:middle line:84%
If I was a little
stronger, maybe you guys

00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:32.550 align:middle line:84%
would still have another
lawyer in the world.

00:04:32.550 --> 00:04:38.360 align:middle line:84%
But for me, I needed to separate
myself from that consciousness.

00:04:38.360 --> 00:04:41.180 align:middle line:84%
But knowing you can be
loving, whatever your role

00:04:41.180 --> 00:04:43.550 align:middle line:90%
is, there's God everywhere.

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:46.310 align:middle line:90%
There's love everywhere.

00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:50.500 align:middle line:84%
So if anyone is wondering,
can I give this up?

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:52.450 align:middle line:90%
Can I surrender?

00:04:52.450 --> 00:04:55.720 align:middle line:84%
Can I give myself a chance
to just let whatever's

00:04:55.720 --> 00:04:58.060 align:middle line:90%
in me come out of me?

00:04:58.060 --> 00:04:59.200 align:middle line:90%
Do it.

00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:00.600 align:middle line:90%
There is no downside.

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:04.000 align:middle line:84%
There is no downside to
becoming more of who you are.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.650 align:middle line:84%
You could always go back
to the security blanket,

00:05:08.650 --> 00:05:09.850 align:middle line:90%
if you want to.

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:11.680 align:middle line:90%
But you don't want to.

00:05:11.680 --> 00:05:13.060 align:middle line:90%
You won't want to.

00:05:13.060 --> 00:05:17.050 align:middle line:84%
Surrender to the biggest that
you can think in yourself,

00:05:17.050 --> 00:05:18.300 align:middle line:90%
whatever you want to call it--

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:22.870 align:middle line:84%
God, Allah, Jesus, whatever you
want to call it, the goddess.

00:05:22.870 --> 00:05:24.010 align:middle line:90%
It's all one.

00:05:24.010 --> 00:05:26.290 align:middle line:90%
Surrender to it.

00:05:26.290 --> 00:05:28.690 align:middle line:84%
Find places to
love in your life.

00:05:28.690 --> 00:05:29.910 align:middle line:90%
How beautiful it is for me.

00:05:29.910 --> 00:05:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I have this incredible
five-year-old

00:05:32.650 --> 00:05:36.160 align:middle line:84%
that I have in my life,
and he just evokes my love.

00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:37.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't really have
to do anything.

00:05:37.660 --> 00:05:40.120 align:middle line:84%
It just-- just being
around him, it's so easy.

00:05:40.120 --> 00:05:44.440 align:middle line:84%
It comes out so easy with your
children, with your friends,

00:05:44.440 --> 00:05:46.030 align:middle line:90%
with people you love.

00:05:46.030 --> 00:05:49.810 align:middle line:84%
Just let them evoke your
love, and for all of us,

00:05:49.810 --> 00:05:52.000 align:middle line:84%
we have those two
sides of the coin.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:55.010 align:middle line:84%
We all-- we need to
share love in some sense,

00:05:55.010 --> 00:05:59.080 align:middle line:84%
and then we have our own unique,
individual way of doing it.

00:05:59.080 --> 00:06:01.750 align:middle line:84%
This is my way,
and it's given me--

00:06:01.750 --> 00:06:03.367 align:middle line:90%
it's given me everything.

00:06:03.367 --> 00:06:07.350 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.350 --> 00:06:11.410 align:middle line:84%
When I die now, I'll say, all
right, I had those moments.

00:06:11.410 --> 00:06:12.790 align:middle line:90%
I had a clue.

00:06:12.790 --> 00:06:15.060 align:middle line:84%
I got a taste of what
it was to be alive,

00:06:15.060 --> 00:06:16.650 align:middle line:90%
and that's for everybody.

00:06:16.650 --> 00:06:21.430 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:21.430 --> 00:06:22.390 align:middle line:90%


00:06:22.390 --> 00:06:23.740 align:middle line:90%
>> I grew up on Long Island.

00:06:23.740 --> 00:06:29.920 align:middle line:84%
I was the three-sport jock
in school, a Yankee fan.

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:31.904 align:middle line:84%
I went to college in
University of Buffalo.

00:06:31.904 --> 00:06:33.070 align:middle line:90%
I was in the peace movement.

00:06:33.070 --> 00:06:35.540 align:middle line:90%
I marched in Washington.

00:06:35.540 --> 00:06:37.420 align:middle line:84%
My best friend's
girlfriend, Alison Krauss,

00:06:37.420 --> 00:06:39.940 align:middle line:84%
was shot and killed
in May of 1970

00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:42.670 align:middle line:84%
by the part-time soldiers,
the National Guard,

00:06:42.670 --> 00:06:44.470 align:middle line:84%
protesting the secret
bombings in Cambodia.

00:06:44.470 --> 00:06:47.060 align:middle line:90%


00:06:47.060 --> 00:06:48.959 align:middle line:84%
But I found that
fighting for peace

00:06:48.959 --> 00:06:50.500 align:middle line:84%
was a kind of
contradiction in terms,

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:52.860 align:middle line:90%
and I wanted to become peace.

00:06:52.860 --> 00:06:57.760 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:00.655 align:middle line:90%


00:07:00.655 --> 00:07:05.220 align:middle line:84%
I experimented with all kinds
of consciousness expansion,

00:07:05.220 --> 00:07:09.840 align:middle line:84%
Gestalt workshops, encounter
groups, psychology, philosophy,

00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:11.850 align:middle line:90%
yoga, meditation in college.

00:07:11.850 --> 00:07:14.250 align:middle line:84%
And then in 1971,
when I graduated,

00:07:14.250 --> 00:07:17.880 align:middle line:84%
instead of pursuing these
things in graduate school,

00:07:17.880 --> 00:07:19.350 align:middle line:90%
I took to the road.

00:07:19.350 --> 00:07:21.780 align:middle line:90%
I flew to England.

00:07:21.780 --> 00:07:25.410 align:middle line:84%
I hitchhiked across Europe
during the summer, all the way

00:07:25.410 --> 00:07:26.720 align:middle line:90%
to Greece.

00:07:26.720 --> 00:07:29.067 align:middle line:84%
And I still was
seeking eastward.

00:07:29.067 --> 00:07:31.650 align:middle line:84%
I was being pulled eastward, as
if being pulled home, I think,

00:07:31.650 --> 00:07:33.410 align:middle line:90%
although I didn't know it then.

00:07:33.410 --> 00:07:38.280 align:middle line:84%
I took a slow boat from Rhodes
in Greece over to Turkey

00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:43.510 align:middle line:84%
and took public transportation
through Turkey, Afghanistan,

00:07:43.510 --> 00:07:46.430 align:middle line:84%
Iran, which was
open then, Pakistan,

00:07:46.430 --> 00:07:49.870 align:middle line:84%
and ended up in India
in August of 1971,

00:07:49.870 --> 00:07:52.140 align:middle line:84%
and began my spiritual
quest in earnest,

00:07:52.140 --> 00:07:55.290 align:middle line:84%
going through a Buddhist--
a 10-day insight meditation

00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:57.960 align:middle line:84%
retreat at that time, which
set me on my Buddhist path.

00:07:57.960 --> 00:08:03.383 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:08:03.383 --> 00:08:09.800 align:middle line:90%


00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:14.550 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been in many ashrams
and monasteries and meditation

00:08:14.550 --> 00:08:18.380 align:middle line:84%
retreats and pilgrimages
during that time

00:08:18.380 --> 00:08:20.970 align:middle line:90%
in the first half of the '70s.

00:08:20.970 --> 00:08:23.780 align:middle line:84%
And I learned a little bit of
Tibetan, Hindi, and Nepali,

00:08:23.780 --> 00:08:24.580 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:08:24.580 --> 00:08:27.960 align:middle line:84%
Finally, I tried to buckle
down and learn Tibetan.

00:08:27.960 --> 00:08:30.810 align:middle line:84%
And I was doing-- learning
many meditation techniques

00:08:30.810 --> 00:08:31.830 align:middle line:90%
and different--

00:08:31.830 --> 00:08:34.049 align:middle line:84%
from different
teachers and practices,

00:08:34.049 --> 00:08:36.539 align:middle line:84%
which I did every day, and
I've been meditating every day

00:08:36.539 --> 00:08:39.120 align:middle line:84%
since then, since
1971, meditation

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.130 align:middle line:90%
being my main practice.

00:08:41.130 --> 00:08:47.070 align:middle line:84%
But somehow it wasn't really as
transformative as I expected.

00:08:47.070 --> 00:08:50.760 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I had some unreal
expectations about this,

00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:53.730 align:middle line:84%
feeling like that I would meet
a guru and get enlightened

00:08:53.730 --> 00:08:57.360 align:middle line:84%
or that after meditating for
a month in silent retreat,

00:08:57.360 --> 00:09:00.660 align:middle line:84%
doing nothing else, that I'd
get enlightened or find peace.

00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:03.170 align:middle line:90%


00:09:03.170 --> 00:09:05.480 align:middle line:84%
Everybody had said,
don't be too ambitious.

00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:06.710 align:middle line:90%
Don't expect too much.

00:09:06.710 --> 00:09:08.270 align:middle line:90%
It's a lifetime journey.

00:09:08.270 --> 00:09:12.102 align:middle line:84%
It takes many lifetimes
to enlightenment.

00:09:12.102 --> 00:09:16.250 align:middle line:84%
Then I met my root guru, as
we call in Tibetan, the Buddha

00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:20.540 align:middle line:84%
Karmapa, Yawa Karmapa,
in Darjeeling,

00:09:20.540 --> 00:09:24.190 align:middle line:84%
and followed him back to his
home monastery in Sikkim.

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:27.460 align:middle line:84%
Of course, he is from Tibet, but
he had to leave Tibet in 1959

00:09:27.460 --> 00:09:29.524 align:middle line:90%
before the Chinese invasion.

00:09:29.524 --> 00:09:33.040 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:39.370 align:middle line:84%
One day, the karmapa was giving
an empowerment initiation

00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:41.260 align:middle line:84%
and introducing
the nature of mind,

00:09:41.260 --> 00:09:43.600 align:middle line:84%
as we call it in
Tibetan, a transmission,

00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:48.826 align:middle line:84%
introducing oneself to one's
true nature, Buddha nature.

00:09:48.826 --> 00:09:51.450 align:middle line:84%
And he was sitting on his seat,
and there were just a few of us

00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:54.980 align:middle line:84%
there, close disciples,
some tuchus and Tibet lamas

00:09:54.980 --> 00:09:57.530 align:middle line:84%
and one or two Westerners
who lived there

00:09:57.530 --> 00:10:02.390 align:middle line:84%
and who were somewhat
experienced, slightly advanced,

00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:04.950 align:middle line:90%
initiation empowerment.

00:10:04.950 --> 00:10:09.710 align:middle line:84%
And when I looked at my guru,
the karmapa, and our eyes

00:10:09.710 --> 00:10:17.760 align:middle line:84%
met, and he held up a crystal,
and suddenly, everything

00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:19.830 align:middle line:90%
dissolved and was gone.

00:10:19.830 --> 00:10:22.680 align:middle line:90%
And he and I were totally one.

00:10:22.680 --> 00:10:28.830 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that his Buddha
mind and my original nature

00:10:28.830 --> 00:10:30.450 align:middle line:90%
were absolutely one.

00:10:30.450 --> 00:10:33.780 align:middle line:84%
And myself and
him and the Buddha

00:10:33.780 --> 00:10:36.870 align:middle line:84%
were absolutely and totally
one, since the beginning time

00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:40.950 align:middle line:90%
in primordial truth.

00:10:40.950 --> 00:10:43.820 align:middle line:84%
And it was as if
everything he was and had

00:10:43.820 --> 00:10:46.670 align:middle line:84%
was pouring into
me, like standing

00:10:46.670 --> 00:10:50.190 align:middle line:90%
in front of Niagara Falls.

00:10:50.190 --> 00:10:51.457 align:middle line:90%
And yet it was reciprocal.

00:10:51.457 --> 00:10:52.540 align:middle line:90%
It was sort of in and out.

00:10:52.540 --> 00:10:53.250 align:middle line:90%
It was pouring in.

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:55.590 align:middle line:84%
It was also pouring out of
me, as if he was looking out

00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:57.980 align:middle line:90%
through my eyes.

00:10:57.980 --> 00:11:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And it was as if the Buddha was
pouring through him into me.

00:11:01.870 --> 00:11:06.390 align:middle line:84%
And there was really
a timeless moment

00:11:06.390 --> 00:11:10.740 align:middle line:84%
that lasted for quite
a while, perhaps half

00:11:10.740 --> 00:11:11.720 align:middle line:90%
an hour or an hour.

00:11:11.720 --> 00:11:13.860 align:middle line:84%
But I was in that state
while he continued

00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:16.860 align:middle line:84%
with the bell, the crystal,
and the other parts

00:11:16.860 --> 00:11:19.020 align:middle line:84%
of the tantric ritual,
the introduction

00:11:19.020 --> 00:11:20.854 align:middle line:90%
to the true nature of our mind.

00:11:20.854 --> 00:11:25.694 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:11:25.694 --> 00:11:31.520 align:middle line:90%


00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:36.410 align:middle line:84%
And during that time, it was
as if he was me, and I was him.

00:11:36.410 --> 00:11:38.120 align:middle line:84%
And I realized there
was nothing outside

00:11:38.120 --> 00:11:42.770 align:middle line:84%
to get, nothing more to
look for, nothing to find,

00:11:42.770 --> 00:11:45.830 align:middle line:84%
nothing missing, that I was
perfect and complete just

00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:46.790 align:middle line:90%
as I am.

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:48.680 align:middle line:84%
The jewel in the
lotus, the light

00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:50.180 align:middle line:84%
is found right here
in the darkness.

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:52.475 align:middle line:90%
Shadows are nothing but light.

00:11:52.475 --> 00:11:54.600 align:middle line:84%
We can make friends with
ourselves, even the shadow

00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:56.700 align:middle line:90%
and dark sides of our psyche.

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:59.280 align:middle line:84%
And seeing the Buddha in him
and seeing the Buddha in me,

00:11:59.280 --> 00:12:02.840 align:middle line:84%
seeing the Buddha in everyone
became reality for me.

00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:04.761 align:middle line:84%
And that totally
transformed my life.

00:12:04.761 --> 00:12:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And when I say "see
the Buddha in others,"

00:12:06.510 --> 00:12:08.100 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean the
Buddhist Buddha.

00:12:08.100 --> 00:12:11.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean the divine, the
light, seeing the Godhead

00:12:11.730 --> 00:12:14.510 align:middle line:90%
in everyone and everything.

00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:16.450 align:middle line:84%
And that totally
transformed my life,

00:12:16.450 --> 00:12:19.730 align:middle line:84%
and I've never been
the same since.

00:12:19.730 --> 00:12:23.650 align:middle line:84%
And I can't really
say how that happened.

00:12:23.650 --> 00:12:25.507 align:middle line:84%
Of course, the
practices that I did

00:12:25.507 --> 00:12:27.090 align:middle line:84%
must have had something
to do with it,

00:12:27.090 --> 00:12:28.977 align:middle line:84%
but when the Karma
ripens, it's not

00:12:28.977 --> 00:12:30.810 align:middle line:84%
just a matter of what
you do or any strategy

00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:34.320 align:middle line:84%
you have in spiritual
practice and spiritual life.

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:37.230 align:middle line:84%
There's also some kind
of karmic ripening

00:12:37.230 --> 00:12:40.980 align:middle line:84%
or grace or kind of
luck, but yet practice

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:42.630 align:middle line:90%
makes us more lucky.

00:12:42.630 --> 00:12:45.160 align:middle line:90%
That I can promise you.

00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:48.300 align:middle line:10%
So I found that
this was, perhaps,

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:51.600 align:middle line:10%
the most transformative
experience in my life,

00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:52.900 align:middle line:10%
and I'll never forget that.

00:12:52.900 --> 00:12:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's as real
today as it was then.

00:12:55.140 --> 00:12:58.826 align:middle line:84%
I can see his eyes on
me and in me right now.

